## 3. DSL SPECIFICATION

### DSL Syntax Format
```
[object_type].[property] = [value] | [frame_range]
[effect_type].[effect_name]([params]) | [frame_range]
keyframe @ frame [frame_number] { [properties] }
```

### Example DSL Code
```
shape.circle(x=100, y=100, r=50, color=#FF0000, duration=1000ms) | frame(0-30)
shape.rectangle(x=200, y=150, w=100, h=80, color=#00FF00, fillType=gradient) | frame(10-60)
effect.opacity(value=0.5, easing=ease-out) | frame(0-15)
effect.rotation_3d(x=45, y=30, z=60, easing=ease-in-out) | frame(20-50)
effect.blur(radius=10, type=gaussian) | frame(25-40)
text.render(content="CODMATION", font="RobotoMono", size=48, color=#FFFFFF) | frame(0-120)
keyframe @ frame 0 { x=0, y=0, scale=1.0 }
keyframe @ frame 30 { x=500, y=300, scale=1.5 }
path.bezier(points=[(0,0), (100,50), (200,0)], stroke=2, color=#0000FF) | frame(0-90)
```

### Supported DSL Elements

#### Shapes
- `circle(x, y, r, color, fillType)`
- `rectangle(x, y, w, h, color, fillType, cornerRadius)`
- `polygon(points, color, fillType)`
- `line(x1, y1, x2, y2, strokeWidth, color)`
- `bezier(points, strokeWidth, color, fillType)`
- `ellipse(x, y, rx, ry, color, fillType, rotation)`
- `path(svgPath, strokeWidth, color, fillType)`
- `text(content, font, size, color, x, y, rotation)`

#### Effects (30+)
- **Opacity:** opacity(value, easing)
- **Rotation:** rotation_2d(angle, easing), rotation_3d(x, y, z, easing)
- **Blur:** blur(radius, type: gaussian|directional), motion_blur(intensity, direction, type: shutter|transform)
- **Shadow:** drop_shadow(offsetX, offsetY, radius, color, opacity)
- **Glow:** outer_glow(radius, color, opacity), inner_glow(radius, color, opacity)
- **Color:** hue_shift(angle), saturation(value), brightness_contrast(brightness, contrast), color_grade(preset), color_tint(color, intensity), color_wash(color, intensity)
- **Distortion:** chromatic_distortion(intensity, direction), pixelation(blockSize), posterization(levels), film_grain(intensity)
- **Transform:** position(x, y, easing), scale(sx, sy, easing), skew(skewX, skewY), shear(shearX, shearY)
- **Blending:** blend_mode(mode: multiply|screen|overlay|etc), masking(type: inverted|alpha|luma)
- **Speed:** speed_ramp(easing: ease-in|ease-out, curve)

#### Keyframes
```
keyframe @ frame [number] { property=value, property=value }
```

#### Animation Properties
- `duration` - milliseconds or frames
- `easing` - linear, ease-in, ease-out, ease-in-out, cubic-bezier(x1,y1,x2,y2)
- `loop` - repeat count or infinite
- `delay` - start delay in ms
- `frame_range` - frame(start-end)

